LEMAR:
Nobody's drowning.
This is not a wig.

57:42.359 --> 57:45.362
This is an inspired
Josephine Baker look.

57:45.395 --> 57:46.997
BLANCA:
Let them know, let them know.

57:47.031 --> 57:48.666
LEMAR:
Okay.

57:48.699 --> 57:51.836
Next time, you need
to make them kids stick around

57:51.869 --> 57:54.204
and help you clean up
before they go out to the club.

57:54.238 --> 57:55.840
Nah, they need to go out
and be young.

57:55.873 --> 57:58.008
-It's been a very rough week.
-Who you telling?

57:58.042 --> 58:01.211
I need to go out
and shake my ass, too.

58:01.245 --> 58:04.181
Oh. Are you sure them
old-ass knees gonna let you?

58:04.214 --> 58:05.182
I'm being serious.

58:05.215 --> 58:06.183
I know.

58:06.216 --> 58:08.185
(chuckles)

58:08.218 --> 58:11.556
I've been holding on to a lot
of stress for way too long.

58:11.589 --> 58:14.358
Listen, I like an empty house,
nice and peaceful.

58:14.391 --> 58:16.026
Just me and my thoughts.

58:16.060 --> 58:17.361
They don't scare you?

58:17.394 --> 58:19.363
Sometimes.

58:19.396 --> 58:22.366
But I got my friends
to lift me up.

58:22.399 --> 58:25.069
And I will be here
to do the same.

58:30.908 --> 58:33.243
That cup is clean.

58:33.277 --> 58:35.245
Just fill it up.

58:35.279 --> 58:37.414
I'm thirsty.

58:44.922 --> 58:47.925
Now, where in the hell
did you get those?

58:50.460 --> 58:53.898
After the funeral
I went to see Judy.

58:53.931 --> 58:56.934
I figured it's time
I started taking these.

59:03.941 --> 59:05.409
What made you change your mind?

59:05.442 --> 59:08.946
I was looking at the children.

59:08.979 --> 59:10.748
Full of dreams,

59:10.781 --> 59:12.750
thinking they have
all the time in the world.

59:12.783 --> 59:17.287
And I'm standing over here
trying to stay alive.

59:18.956 --> 59:21.458
I don't want to go
to my casket...

59:21.491 --> 59:22.927
with any regrets.

59:22.960 --> 59:26.130
Nothing left undone...

59:26.163 --> 59:28.332
or unsaid.

59:30.334 --> 59:32.803
(crying):
Candy's--

59:32.837 --> 59:36.440
Candy's death reminded me

59:36.473 --> 59:38.976
that life is so precious.

59:40.645 --> 59:43.814
And I don't want to waste mine.
I don't want to waste it.

59:46.984 --> 59:49.654
(exhales)
And...

59:51.021 --> 59:54.324
I have an obligation
to fight for my life

59:54.358 --> 59:56.460
just as much as I've been
fighting for Act Up.

59:56.493 --> 59:58.495
(both laugh)

1:00:01.999 --> 1:00:04.001
Pray, I'm so proud of you.

1:00:05.535 --> 1:00:08.338
(sighs)

1:00:17.014 --> 1:00:18.482
Oh, it's a party now?

1:00:18.515 --> 1:00:20.651
No, more like a toast.

1:00:20.685 --> 1:00:23.220
(laughing)

1:00:32.196 --> 1:00:34.198
To life.

1:00:36.200 --> 1:00:37.868
To life.

1:02:26.476 --> 1:02:28.478
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

1:02:30.414 --> 1:02:34.451
The world is singing about
a movement we created.

1:02:34.484 --> 1:02:35.452
Everything
is about to change.

1:02:37.321 --> 1:02:38.622
Where you gettin'
all this money from?

1:02:38.655 --> 1:02:40.657
I don't owe you
an explanation.

1:02:40.690 --> 1:02:43.093
-You always so jealous.
-I can't even trust you.

1:02:43.127 --> 1:02:46.997
There are things
that are more important
than trophies.

1:02:47.031 --> 1:02:49.133
All I got are my children.

1:02:49.166 --> 1:02:50.134
-(shutter clicks)
-This is your dream.

1:02:52.837 --> 1:02:54.771
-I want a shot.
-(shutter clicks)

1:02:56.006 --> 1:02:57.174
ANNOUNCER: Pose.

1:02:57.207 --> 1:02:59.709
All new,
Tuesdays at 10:00 on FX.

1:03:03.180 --> 1:03:05.382
CISSY: You said
you had it under control.

1:03:06.951 --> 1:03:08.185
It's up to you...

1:03:10.888 --> 1:03:12.356
to protect everyone.

1:03:15.725 --> 1:03:16.994
Can you do it or not?

1:03:17.027 --> 1:03:18.495
ANNOUNCER: Snowfall.

1:03:18.528 --> 1:03:21.365
Season premiere, July 10 on FX.

1:03:23.733 --> 1:03:26.536
(shrieks)
Rocket pack!

1:03:26.570 --> 1:03:28.906
You know how much fuel
you just wasted?

1:03:29.006 --> 1:03:32.843
I don't know. How much paint
did Michelangelo waste
on the Sistine Chapel?

1:03:32.877 --> 1:03:34.845
ANNOUNCER: Archer 1999.

1:03:34.879 --> 1:03:37.481
All new,
Wednesdays at 10:00 on FXX.

1:03:38.582 --> 1:03:40.384
Since this is
your first time,

1:03:40.417 --> 1:03:42.752
why don't you tell us
something about yourself?

1:03:44.754 --> 1:03:46.090
I don't like cats.

1:03:47.024 --> 1:03:49.226
Okay.
Martha, what about you?

1:03:50.027 --> 1:03:52.029
Well, Chip stole mine.

1:03:53.730 --> 1:03:55.099
ANNOUNCER: Baskets.

1:03:55.199 --> 1:03:57.767
All new,
Thursdays at 10:00 on FX.

1:03:59.603 --> 1:04:01.238
WOMAN (distorted):
I heard he's a savior.

1:04:01.271 --> 1:04:02.907
-WOMAN 2:
I heard he's a mutant.
-WOMAN 3: He's a god.

1:04:02.940 --> 1:04:04.608
Open your eyes.

1:04:04.708 --> 1:04:06.443
I help people
open their minds.

1:04:06.543 --> 1:04:08.778
-Is this a cult?
-Ticktock, little birdie.

1:04:10.614 --> 1:04:13.417
-I'm a good person.
-You end the world.

1:04:13.450 --> 1:04:14.919
SWITCH: Why do you
need to time travel?

1:04:14.952 --> 1:04:17.087
It's about saving lives,
starting with mine.

1:04:20.724 --> 1:04:24.895
How do you surprise someone
who can go back in time
and warn himself?

1:04:25.795 --> 1:04:26.964
ANNOUNCER: Legion.

1:04:27.064 --> 1:04:28.966
All new,
Mondays at 10:00 on FX.
